Don Farmer's Apple Cake

Cake:
2 c sugar
1 1/2 c oil
3 eggs
3 c flour
2 tsp vanilla
1 tsp baking soda
2 tsp cinnamon
2/3 tsp nutmeg
1/2 tsp salt
3 c chopped apples (~3-4 medium)

Preheat oven to 325F. Grease and sugar a tube or bundt pan. In a large bowl, combine the sugar and oil. Beat in the eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla. Add flour, baking soda, and spices. Batter will be thick. Add apples. Spoon into prepared pan and bake for 1 hr 15 min. After cooled, remove from pan and place on cake plate with crisp side up. 

Glaze:
4 tbsp cream
4 tbsp butter
4 tbsp sugar
4 tbsp brown sugar

Melt ingredients in a saucepan, boil for 1 min. Spoon over cake and serve.
